    <node id="Artificial Neural Networks">
      <data key="d0">Artificial Neural Networks</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) are computational models inspired by biological learning processes in the brain.&lt;SEP&gt;Artificial Neural Networks are computational models inspired by the human brain, used since the 1950s for various applications.&lt;SEP&gt;Artificial Neural Networks are computational models inspired by the human brain, used for various applications including traffic sign classification.&lt;SEP&gt;Artificial neural networks are computerized systems designed to simulate the way biological neural networks process information.&lt;SEP&gt;Artificial neural networks are computational models inspired by the human brain, known for their application in deep learning and processing complex data.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-85cefddcaecd1949b3492b6883a08ac6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7030ceb5e481db7469c5a663054ab0ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a141800f1c44ebc302d730822f4d8c41&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e301584dbc493504e638dde9613d0a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95ce81b8a88d7af76b627732161bfd8d</data>
