    <node id="Orthogonal Matrix">
      <data key="d0">Orthogonal Matrix</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">An orthogonal matrix is a square matrix whose rows and columns are mutually orthonormal vectors, allowing for cheap computation of inverses.&lt;SEP&gt;An orthogonal matrix is a square matrix whose rows and columns are orthogonal unit vectors, which preserves the dot product.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f81436ceefbaa6d5dc02610dd8127f9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0d3be7ce3dfb930212c12aac0c54ff0</data>
