    <node id="Eigendecomposition">
      <data key="d0">Eigendecomposition</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Eigendecomposition is a mathematical technique used in linear algebra to decompose a matrix into its eigenvalues and eigenvectors.&lt;SEP&gt;Eigendecomposition refers to the process of breaking down a matrix into its eigenvectors and eigenvalues.&lt;SEP&gt;Eigendecomposition is a method of decomposing a matrix into its eigenvalues and eigenvectors, used to analyze the properties of the matrix.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f81436ceefbaa6d5dc02610dd8127f9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0139bf2dedbbf7d4064d9e8be650befc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9a143ce5c66baaa2cee5e90f9622516</data>
