    <node id="Pseudoinverse">
      <data key="d0">Pseudoinverse</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Pseudoinverse is a generalization of the inverse matrix concept, applicable to non-square matrices in linear algebra.&lt;SEP&gt;The pseudoinverse is a mathematical concept used to find solutions to linear equations, especially when dealing with matrices that do not have a unique solution.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0139bf2dedbbf7d4064d9e8be650befc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-443f6360d2d3fc61bef3f5a8c109e2f2</data>
