    <node id="Matrix Inversion">
      <data key="d0">Matrix Inversion</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Matrix inversion is a mathematical method used to find the inverse of a matrix, which is necessary in solving linear equations but is not applicable for singular matrices.&lt;SEP&gt;Matrix Inversion is a mathematical operation that attempts to find the inverse of a matrix, which is defined only for square matrices.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0139bf2dedbbf7d4064d9e8be650befc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e325d64a50359748cfb47987a361fbb1</data>
