    <node id="Diagonal Matrix">
      <data key="d0">Diagonal Matrix</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A diagonal matrix is characterized by having non-zero entries only on its main diagonal, making it computationally efficient for various mathematical operations.&lt;SEP&gt;A diagonal matrix is a special type of matrix where non-zero values are only present on the diagonal, and its pseudoinverse can be computed by taking the reciprocal of non-zero elements.&lt;SEP&gt;A Diagonal Matrix is a type of matrix where the entries outside the main diagonal are all zero.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0139bf2dedbbf7d4064d9e8be650befc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-443f6360d2d3fc61bef3f5a8c109e2f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0403607cb7181d4a13a232d13fec9630</data>
