    <node id="Monte Carlo Methods">
      <data key="d0">Monte Carlo Methods</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Monte Carlo Methods refer to a broad class of computational algorithms that rely on repeated random sampling to obtain numerical results.&lt;SEP&gt;Monte Carlo Methods are statistical techniques that utilize random sampling to obtain numerical results, often used in probabilistic models.&lt;SEP&gt;Monte Carlo Methods relate to statistical sampling techniques discussed in advanced deep learning research.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e50469f832851b636f2df3ba1727f237&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac272cb401529a36c7732284f3da738&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11ce15464424cd55fa29c0ee197674cc</data>
