    <node id="Matrix">
      <data key="d0">Matrix</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A matrix is a mathematical entity defined as a rectangular array of numbers, symbols, or expressions organized in rows and columns. This structured arrangement is fundamental in various mathematical and statistical computations, serving numerous purposes across different fields such as linear algebra, engineering, and machine learning. 

Matrices can be described as two-dimensional arrays where each element is identified by two indices, typically described using uppercase bold letters. They are used to represent linear transformations and systems of equations, providing a means to perform calculations and analyze data. The versatility of matrices is showcased in their ability to represent not only numerical data but also other mathematical objects, making them essential tools in both theoretical and applied mathematics.

Furthermore, in contexts such as artificial intelligence (AI), matrices are applied to organize and structure data points used in training examples. This underscores their significance not just in traditional mathematical settings, but also in modern computational applications, where they enable efficient data representation and manipulation. Overall, matrices serve as a cornerstone of various quantitative disciplines, facilitating the analysis and solution of complex problems through structured numerical representations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1cab33350eba1be65fc00415923198c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f81436ceefbaa6d5dc02610dd8127f9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0139bf2dedbbf7d4064d9e8be650befc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d55b6724597822ab76201288059bd8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-443f6360d2d3fc61bef3f5a8c109e2f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52465e8bb143dc190c7efa3f3e89fda6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d2e722934164a54c6a816c106572c75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88935c9c850ad773b6af22d7912a351e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f2b9c7716a8cfdb253e66aff0aa4394&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e325d64a50359748cfb47987a361fbb1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0403607cb7181d4a13a232d13fec9630</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768911146</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
