    <node id="Nested Hierarchy of Concepts">
      <data key="d0">Nested Hierarchy of Concepts</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">This refers to the framework in deep learning where concepts are organized in terms of simpler and more abstract representations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bd2a057016fddbfc53fb1a5ab4973351</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768911163</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Computational Graph">
      <data key="d0">Computational Graph</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The computational graph is a representation of the computations required to evaluate a model, crucial for understanding its depth and processing capabilities.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bd2a057016fddbfc53fb1a5ab4973351</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768911163</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Probabilistic Modeling Graph">
      <data key="d0">Probabilistic Modeling Graph</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The probabilistic modeling graph refers to the depth of relationships between concepts rather than the depth of the computational process itself, impacting the model's understanding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bd2a057016fddbfc53fb1a5ab4973351</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768911164</data>
