    <node id="Identity Matrix">
      <data key="d0">Identity Matrix</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The identity matrix is a special diagonal matrix where all diagonal entries are equal to one, serving as a multiplicative identity in matrix operations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0403607cb7181d4a13a232d13fec9630</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768911164</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Symmetric Matrix">
      <data key="d0">Symmetric Matrix</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A symmetric matrix is defined by the property that its transposition yields the same matrix, which is often relevant in functions that measure distances.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0403607cb7181d4a13a232d13fec9630</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768911165</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Orthogonal Vectors">
      <data key="d0">Orthogonal Vectors</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Orthogonal vectors are those that intersect at a 90 degree angle, characterized by a dot product of zero when both vectors have non-zero norms.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0403607cb7181d4a13a232d13fec9630</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768911165</data>
