    <node id="Dyslipidaemia">
      <data key="d0">Dyslipidaemia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Dyslipidaemia refers to abnormal levels of lipids in the blood, which can have various secondary causes.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia is a condition characterized by abnormal lipid levels, often present in conjunction with other metabolic disorders.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia refers to abnormal levels of lipids in the blood, contributing to cardiovascular complications in patients with type 2 diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia refers to abnormal lipid levels in the blood that need to be addressed in diabetes management.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia refers to abnormal lipid levels in the blood, which is a concern for patients with diabetes and contributes to cardiovascular risks.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia refers to abnormal lipid levels in the blood, important for cardiovascular risk management in patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia refers to an abnormal amount of lipids in the blood, and management may include lifestyle changes and therapy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915061</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Aspirin Therapy">
      <data key="d0">Aspirin Therapy</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Aspirin therapy is a treatment indicated for secondary prevention in diabetic patients with cardiovascular disease and for primary prevention in at-risk individuals.&lt;SEP&gt;Aspirin therapy involves the use of aspirin for secondary and primary prevention of cardiovascular disease, particularly in diabetic patients.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915061</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cardiovascular Disease">
      <data key="d0">Cardiovascular Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Cardiovascular disease refers to disorders affecting the heart and blood vessels, associated with risk factors such as diabetes and hypertension.&lt;SEP&gt;Cardiovascular disease encompasses various conditions affecting the heart and blood vessels, and is a focus of prevention strategies using aspirin.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915062</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Reye Syndrome">
      <data key="d0">Reye Syndrome</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Reye syndrome is a serious condition associated with aspirin therapy in children, characterized by acute encephalopathy and fatty liver degeneration.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915062</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hypoglycaemia">
      <data key="d0">Hypoglycaemia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hypoglycaemia refers to abnormally low blood glucose levels, which can occur in individuals with diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypoglycaemia is a condition of abnormally low blood glucose levels, often occurring in patients with diabetes, leading to various symptoms.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypoglycaemia is a condition characterized by abnormally low levels of blood glucose, requiring careful management and education for patients and healthcare workers.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915062</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Insulin">
      <data key="d0">Insulin</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Insulin is a hormone crucial for glucose metabolism, and its deficiencies or resistances are primary factors in diabetes mellitus.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a therapeutic method used for diabetes management, particularly when lifestyle modifications are inadequate.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone used in diabetes management that can consistently lower triglycerides but has variable effects on other lipid levels.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone used to regulate blood sugar levels in diabetes patients, significant in managing hypoglycaemia.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone used in diabetes management, with varying action times based on its type.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85ef35aaa38ac4f0c032c8bc3f6df559&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915062</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Oral Hypoglycaemic Agents">
      <data key="d0">Oral Hypoglycaemic Agents</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Oral hypoglycaemic agents are medications for diabetes that lower blood sugar levels, potentially leading to hypoglycaemia.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915062</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Autonomic Neuropathy">
      <data key="d0">Autonomic Neuropathy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Autonomic neuropathy refers to nerve damage affecting involuntary bodily functions, complicating the recognition and recovery from hypoglycaemia.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915062</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Emergency Medical Personnel">
      <data key="d0">Emergency Medical Personnel</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Emergency medical personnel are healthcare providers trained to recognize and treat conditions such as hypoglycaemia in urgent situations.&lt;SEP&gt;Emergency medical personnel are healthcare workers trained to recognize and treat critical conditions like hypoglycaemia and ketoacidosis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915062</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Lipid-Lowering Agents">
      <data key="d0">Lipid-Lowering Agents</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Lipid-lowering agents are medications used to reduce levels of lipids in the blood and are commonly prescribed for managing high LDL.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915062</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Statin">
      <data key="d0">Statin</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Statins are a class of lipid-lowering medications used to lower LDL cholesterol and reduce cardiovascular risk.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915062</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bile Acid-Binding Resin">
      <data key="d0">Bile Acid-Binding Resin</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Bile acid-binding resins are medications that help lower LDL cholesterol by binding to bile acids in the intestine.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915063</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ezetimibe">
      <data key="d0">Ezetimibe</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Ezetimibe is a cholesterol absorption inhibitor used at a dose of 10 mg to help lower cholesterol levels.&lt;SEP&gt;Ezetimibe is a lipid-lowering medication that works by decreasing the absorption of cholesterol from the diet.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915063</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fibrate">
      <data key="d0">Fibrate</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Fibrates are a class of medications used to lower triglyceride levels and increase HDL cholesterol.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915063</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Nicotinic Acid">
      <data key="d0">Nicotinic Acid</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Nicotinic acid is a medication used to manage diabetic dyslipidaemia, capable of raising HDL and lowering triglycerides, but with potential side effects.&lt;SEP&gt;Nicotinic acid is a form of vitamin B3 that can lower LDL and triglyceride levels while raising HDL cholesterol.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915063</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Acute Complications of Diabetes">
      <data key="d0">Acute Complications of Diabetes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Acute complications of diabetes include immediate health issues that can arise from uncontrolled blood glucose levels, such as hypoglycaemia.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915063</data>
