    <node id="Diabetes">
      <data key="d0">Diabetes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Diabetes refers broadly to a group of diseases that result in high blood sugar, with a significant impact on public health and healthcare systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a chronic disease that occurs when the body cannot properly process food for use as energy, leading to high blood sugar levels.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a condition for which individualized medical nutrition therapy is recommended, particularly regarding the management of lipid profiles.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a metabolic disorder characterized by high blood sugar levels, which can lead to a variety of complications including infections and atherosclerosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a chronic condition characterized by high blood sugar levels, which can lead to various complications including neuropathy.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a chronic condition characterized by high blood sugar levels, leading to various health complications requiring preventive measures and education.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2173942c84747feba52cff952903a7f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55d2691a8c714949752d249721fec5e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
