    <node id="Ketoacidosis">
      <data key="d0">Ketoacidosis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Ketoacidosis is a serious complication of diabetes characterized by high levels of ketones in the blood, more common in type 1 diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Ketoacidosis is a serious complication of diabetes characterized by high levels of ketones in the body due to insufficient insulin.&lt;SEP&gt;Ketoacidosis is a serious complication of diabetes, typically affecting type 1 diabetes, where the body produces excess ketones, leading to potentially severe metabolic disturbances.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580</data>
