    <node id="Type 2 Diabetes">
      <data key="d0">Type 2 Diabetes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Type 2 diabetes is a chronic condition characterized by insulin resistance and elevated blood glucose levels, often leading to serious complications.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes is a common form of diabetes, often managed with lifestyle changes and medications.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes is a condition influenced by insulin resistance and is less commonly associated with ketoacidosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes is another variant of diabetes that presents different risks for complications like nephropathy depending on ethnic origin.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes is a metabolic disorder characterized by high blood sugar and insulin resistance, with significant health repercussions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
