    <node id="Hyperglycaemia">
      <data key="d0">Hyperglycaemia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hyperglycaemia is a condition characterized by excessively high blood glucose levels, often associated with diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperglycaemia is a condition characterized by high blood glucose levels, which is relevant in the context of metabolic syndrome and diabetes management.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperglycaemia refers to elevated blood sugar levels, which must be managed to reduce cardiovascular risks.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperglycaemia is a condition characterized by elevated blood glucose levels, often associated with diabetes mellitus.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperglycaemia reflects elevated blood sugar levels which may contribute to the development of complications such as atherosclerosis.</data>
