    <node id="Blood Pressure">
      <data key="d0">Blood Pressure</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Blood pressure is the force of blood against the walls of arteries, measured in mmHg and classified into categories like normal, prehypertension, and hypertension.&lt;SEP&gt;Blood pressure is a vital sign measured to assess cardiovascular health, which is particularly crucial for managing diabetes-related complications.&lt;SEP&gt;Blood pressure is a measurement indicating the force of blood against the walls of the arteries, targeted for management in patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Blood Pressure is a vital sign that should be monitored regularly, especially in patients with diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Blood pressure is a critical health metric that should be monitored in patients with diabetes mellitus to manage complications like nephropathy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
