    <node id="Diabetes Mellitus">
      <data key="d0">Diabetes Mellitus</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Diabetes Mellitus is a chronic noncommunicable disease characterized by persistently high blood sugar levels due to issues related to insulin production or its effectiveness in the body. It is recognized as a significant public health concern and can lead to serious health complications if not managed adequately.

Diabetes Mellitus is categorized into different types, primarily type 1 and type 2 diabetes, each with distinct pathophysiological mechanisms and treatment strategies. Type 1 diabetes is generally characterized by autoimmune destruction of insulin-producing beta cells in the pancreas, leading to absolute insulin deficiency. In contrast, type 2 diabetes involves insulin resistance and relative insulin deficiency and is often associated with obesity and lifestyle factors. 

Management of Diabetes Mellitus is crucial, as it involves continuous monitoring and control of blood glucose levels. Individuals with diabetes must often adopt comprehensive management strategies, which may include dietary adjustments, physical activity, regular blood sugar monitoring, and, in many cases, insulin therapy or other pharmacological interventions to prevent complications. 

Complications associated with poorly managed Diabetes Mellitus can affect various organ systems, including the eyes, kidneys, and cardiovascular system, leading to conditions such as retinopathy, nephropathy, and increased risk of heart disease. The disease impacts metabolic processes not only for carbohydrates but also for fats and proteins, reflecting its systemic nature.

Overall, Diabetes Mellitus encompasses a spectrum of disorders characterized by disturbances in glucose metabolism, necessitating careful management to reduce health risks and improve quality of life.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f15f59b3ff05825a61f252ed8f9a74e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85ef35aaa38ac4f0c032c8bc3f6df559&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4cfbed43aa26af0eef694fecac2177&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25fb88c8ed14936954356d104de095d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8c827cc2249067692290d6a8a0e8018&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b253411e54c35aa95f5f9179723bba3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
