    <node id="Health-Care Providers">
      <data key="d0">Health-Care Providers</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Health-care providers are professionals responsible for delivering medical care and treatment for individuals with conditions like brittle diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus">
      <data key="d0">Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus is a form of diabetes increasingly found in younger populations, contributing to rising health burdens.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus may or may not require insulin and is often a result of insulin secretion defects and insulin resistance.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes mellitus is the most prevalent form, marked by insulin resistance and associated with obesity and metabolic issues.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes mellitus is a prevalent form of diabetes that has been increasing among children and adolescents, particularly due to obesity.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus is a form of diabetes that is often linked to obesity and insulin resistance.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes mellitus is a chronic condition where the body does not use insulin properly, leading to high blood sugar levels.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes mellitus is a form of diabetes associated with obesity and dyslipidaemia, impacting insulin resistance and treatment objectives.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25fb88c8ed14936954356d104de095d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bacterial Infections">
      <data key="d0">Bacterial Infections</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Bacterial infections are health conditions that affect individuals with diabetes, with an increased predisposition in this population.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fungal Infections">
      <data key="d0">Fungal Infections</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Fungal infections are a serious health threat to individuals with diabetes, often arising in poor hygienic surroundings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diabetics">
      <data key="d0">Diabetics</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Diabetics are individuals diagnosed with diabetes, who face heightened risks for various infections and complications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diabetic Nephropathy">
      <data key="d0">Diabetic Nephropathy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Diabetic nephropathy is a kidney complication associated with diabetes that can be aggravated by infections like pyelitis and pyelonephritis.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetic nephropathy is the most common cause of renal failure in diabetes patients and involves various progressive stages.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetic nephropathy is a complication of diabetes characterized by kidney damage and progressive loss of renal function.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4cfbed43aa26af0eef694fecac2177</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Atherosclerosis">
      <data key="d0">Atherosclerosis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Atherosclerosis is a macrovascular complication prevalent in diabetes, leading to increased cardiovascular risks.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hyperinsulinaemia">
      <data key="d0">Hyperinsulinaemia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hyperinsulinaemia denotes an excess of insulin in the blood, which is linked to higher rates of coronary disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Obesity">
      <data key="d0">Obesity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Obesity is a condition that has rapidly increased among children and is a significant contributor to the rise in type 2 diabetes mellitus.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is a condition often linked to increased cardiovascular risk and metabolic disturbances.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is an associated risk factor that requires management in individuals with diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is a condition that aggravates dyslipidaemia and hypertension in patients with diabetes, leading to increased insulin resistance.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity, particularly abdominal obesity, is associated with increased risks of atherosclerosis and diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diabetic Retinopathy">
      <data key="d0">Diabetic Retinopathy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Diabetic retinopathy is a severe complication of diabetes that can lead to blindness and visual impairment.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetic retinopathy is a specific type of retinopathy that occurs in people with diabetes and involves damage to the retina.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetic retinopathy is a complication of diabetes that requires prevention and management strategies to reduce its impact on vision.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915072</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pregnancy">
      <data key="d0">Pregnancy</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">Pregnancy is a condition that women with known diabetes mellitus must consider due to potential risks for diabetic retinopathy.&lt;SEP&gt;Pregnancy presents particular risks for women with diabetes, particularly concerning the progression of diabetic retinopathy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915072</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Chronic Infections">
      <data key="d0">Chronic Infections</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Chronic infections are persistent infections that can lead to severe complications in individuals with diabetes, particularly affecting neuropathic or ischaemic feet.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915072</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Neurogenic Bladder">
      <data key="d0">Neurogenic Bladder</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Neurogenic bladder is a condition that can contribute to urinary tract infections in diabetics.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915072</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hypertension">
      <data key="d0">Hypertension</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hypertension is a medical condition characterized by consistently elevated blood pressure, recognized as a significant risk factor for various cardiovascular diseases. This condition is commonly associated with complications related to type 2 diabetes, as hypertension can exacerbate existing health issues such as kidney damage and atherosclerosis. 

Management of hypertension is essential, especially in individuals with diabetes, where it is often treated through a combination of lifestyle modifications and medications. Addressing hypertension effectively is crucial for preventing serious health complications, thereby highlighting the importance of monitoring and managing blood pressure in patients diagnosed with diabetes. Overall, the interplay between hypertension and diabetes illustrates the necessity of integrated healthcare strategies to enhance patient outcomes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4cfbed43aa26af0eef694fecac2177&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915072</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tuberculosis">
      <data key="d0">Tuberculosis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Tuberculosis is a serious health threat associated with diabetes, affecting the respiratory and other organ systems.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915072</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Micro-Vascular Complications">
      <data key="d0">Micro-Vascular Complications</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Micro-vascular complications are health issues emerging from type 2 diabetes, affecting small blood vessels and leading to conditions like retinopathy and nephropathy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915072</data>
