    </node>
    <node id="Eastern Mediterranean Region">
      <data key="d0">Eastern Mediterranean Region</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">The Eastern Mediterranean Region is a geographical area involved in the WHO's focus on noncommunicable diseases like diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is experiencing a rapid increase in diabetes incidence, now determining health priorities in that area.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is a geographical area noted for high diabetes mellitus and IGT prevalence rates.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is a geographical area that includes several countries, characterized by a diverse population and high diabetes prevalence.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is the area where screening for type 2 diabetes in children is recommended under certain conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean region is one of the WHO regions mentioned regarding diabetes prevention and management guidelines.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is a geographical area experiencing a rising prevalence of type 2 diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f15f59b3ff05825a61f252ed8f9a74e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85ef35aaa38ac4f0c032c8bc3f6df559&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8c827cc2249067692290d6a8a0e8018&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b253411e54c35aa95f5f9179723bba3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915072</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="High-Risk Characteristics">
      <data key="d0">High-Risk Characteristics</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">High-risk characteristics refer to specific factors that increase the likelihood of developing type 2 diabetes, including ethnicity and age.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915072</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ethnicity">
      <data key="d0">Ethnicity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Ethnicity in this context refers to specific population groups, such as Pacific Islanders and Australian Aborigines, that show high prevalence of type 2 diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915072</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Insulin Resistance">
      <data key="d0">Insulin Resistance</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Insulin resistance is a condition often associated with metabolic syndrome, impacting glucose tolerance and diabetes risk.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin resistance is a metabolic condition associated with increased cardiovascular risk and multiple metabolic abnormalities.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin resistance is a condition where cells fail to respond effectively to insulin, contributing to the development of type 2 diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915072</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Gestational Diabetes Mellitus">
      <data key="d0">Gestational Diabetes Mellitus</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Gestational diabetes mellitus is a condition of high blood sugar that occurs during pregnancy, which can increase the risk of type 2 diabetes later in life.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915073</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="HbA1c">
      <data key="d0">HbA1c</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">HbA1c is a laboratory test that reflects average blood glucose levels over the past two to three months, used for diabetes management.&lt;SEP&gt;HbA1c is a measure of average blood glucose levels over the past two to three months, commonly used to monitor diabetes control.&lt;SEP&gt;HbA1c is a measure of blood glucose control over time, important for monitoring diabetic patients' overall health.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915073</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study">
      <data key="d0">United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">The United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study is a major diabetes research project that investigates the long-term effects and management of diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;The United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study is a significant research initiative that investigates the relationship between diabetes management and complications, including retinopathy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915073</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diabetes Control and Complications Trial">
      <data key="d0">Diabetes Control and Complications Trial</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">The Diabetes Control and Complications Trial is a significant clinical trial that studied the effects of improved blood glucose control on diabetes complications.&lt;SEP&gt;The Diabetes Control and Complications Trial was a significant study in the USA highlighting the benefits of blood glucose control in type 1 diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;The Diabetes Control and Complications Trial is a clinical study assessing the effects of treatment strategies on the complications of diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-942e000d0de99e8628ab9c8bcbe83419</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915073</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Oral Anti-Hyperglycaemic Agents">
      <data key="d0">Oral Anti-Hyperglycaemic Agents</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Oral anti-hyperglycaemic agents are medications used to lower blood sugar levels in patients with type 2 diabetes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915073</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fructosamine">
      <data key="d0">Fructosamine</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Fructosamine is a blood test that measures average blood glucose levels but is not a substitute for HbA1c testing.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915073</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Polycystic Ovarian Syndrome">
      <data key="d0">Polycystic Ovarian Syndrome</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Polycystic ovarian syndrome is a condition that affects women's hormone levels and is associated with insulin resistance and diabetes risk.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915073</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Acanthosis Nigricans">
      <data key="d0">Acanthosis Nigricans</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Acanthosis nigricans is a skin disorder characterized by dark, velvety patches, often associated with insulin resistance.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915073</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Body Mass Index">
      <data key="d0">Body Mass Index</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Body mass index is a measure of body fat based on height and weight, used to assess overweight and obesity status, which are risk factors for type 2 diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Body mass index (BMI) is used as a measure of obesity, where a BMI ≥ 25 kg/m² indicates overweight and a BMI ≥ 30 kg/m² indicates obesity.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915074</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Impaired Glucose Tolerance (IGT)">
      <data key="d0">Impaired Glucose Tolerance (IGT)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Impaired Glucose Tolerance (IGT) is a stage of glucose regulation that indicates a risk for developing diabetes mellitus.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915074</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Impaired Fasting Glycaemia (IFG)">
      <data key="d0">Impaired Fasting Glycaemia (IFG)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Impaired Fasting Glycaemia (IFG) represents a clinical stage indicating fasting glucose levels above normal but below the diabetes threshold.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915074</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Malnutrition-Related Diabetes (MRDM)">
      <data key="d0">Malnutrition-Related Diabetes (MRDM)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Malnutrition-Related Diabetes (MRDM) is proposed to be deleted, as evidence does not convincingly support diabetes caused by malnutrition.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915074</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Protein-Deficient Pancreatic Diabetes (PDPD or PDDM)">
      <data key="d0">Protein-Deficient Pancreatic Diabetes (PDPD or PDDM)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Protein-Deficient Pancreatic Diabetes (PDPD or PDDM) is suggested as a modified form of diabetes arising from malnutrition.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915074</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Gestational Diabetes">
      <data key="d0">Gestational Diabetes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Gestational Diabetes encompasses conditions that were previously classified under gestational impaired glucose tolerance and gestational diabetes mellitus.&lt;SEP&gt;Gestational diabetes is a form of diabetes that develops during pregnancy and can lead to various health issues for the mother and child.&lt;SEP&gt;Gestational diabetes is a type of diabetes that occurs during pregnancy and requires specific management strategies.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915074</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cystic Fibrosis">
      <data key="d0">Cystic Fibrosis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Cystic Fibrosis is a specific condition that can cause ß-cell destruction leading to diabetes mellitus, distinct from idiopathic forms.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915075</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Mitochondrial Defect">
      <data key="d0">Mitochondrial Defect</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Mitochondrial Defect refers to a specific cause of ß-cell destruction that can lead to diabetes, recognized in the classification of diabetes types.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915075</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fibrocalculous Pancreatic Diabetes (FCPD)">
      <data key="d0">Fibrocalculous Pancreatic Diabetes (FCPD)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Fibrocalculous Pancreatic Diabetes (FCPD) is a condition now classified as fibrocalculous pancreatopathy which may lead to diabetes mellitus.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915075</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Retinopathy">
      <data key="d0">Retinopathy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Retinopathy refers to damage to the retina of the eye, commonly associated with diabetes, which can threaten vision.&lt;SEP&gt;Retinopathy is a sight-threatening condition that can be prevented or delayed through awareness and timely treatment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915075</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ophthalmologist">
      <data key="d0">Ophthalmologist</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">An ophthalmologist is a medical doctor specializing in eye care, responsible for retinal screening in diabetic patients.&lt;SEP&gt;An ophthalmologist is a medical doctor specializing in eye care and surgery, essential for screening and treatment of diabetic eye disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915075</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Primary Care Physician">
      <data key="d0">Primary Care Physician</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">A primary care physician is a healthcare provider responsible for general health monitoring and initial screening for conditions like diabetic retinopathy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1768915075</data>
