    <node id="World Health Organization">
      <data key="d0">World Health Organization</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The World Health Organization is a global health authority that provides public health guidelines and oversees healthcare issues like diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization is an international public health agency that estimated the global burden of diabetes and prioritizes its control.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization (WHO) is the international body that surveys diabetes prevalence and guidelines for management.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization (WHO) is a governing body responsible for public health issues, including defining and addressing diabetes mellitus.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization (WHO) oversees global health issues, including reports and guidelines on diabetes prevention and control.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization is a specialized agency of the United Nations responsible for international public health.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f15f59b3ff05825a61f252ed8f9a74e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85ef35aaa38ac4f0c032c8bc3f6df559&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b253411e54c35aa95f5f9179723bba3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57782c3301473bc8e8dafd9683ab2650&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-942e000d0de99e8628ab9c8bcbe83419</data>
